                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d320">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/1197: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-05T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 5, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 5—9:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>58. Referring to my telegram No. 55, August 26, 11 a.m. and Department’s 46,
                    August 27, 2 p.m.<note n="98" xml:id="d320fn98">See footnote 92, <ref
                            target="#pg_319">p. 319</ref>.</note> Having received no reply to my
                    personal note of August 29, I telephoned Señor Vidal today. He stated it was
                    wholly impossible to consider the release of American prisoners but he would be
                    glad to receive any concrete proposal for their exchange. My impression is that
                    Burgos authorities do not want to act in this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
